The paper deals with the computational complexity of approximating the partition function of the hardcore model, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of random graphs, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of the second moment method and the analysis of the reconstruction problem on the tree suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
